The paper discusses a federated database system that addresses privacy concerns and regulatory compliance issues, which are common topics in the database (cs.DB) and security and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The system also uses secure multiparty computation (SMC), which is a technique commonly used in distributed systems (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) for privacy-preserving data analysis. Finally, the paper introduces a framework for executing PDN queries, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) aspects such as query optimization and translation.
